Incorrect	
In 1066, an invasion led by William, the Duke of Normandy (in what is now northern France), defeated Harold, the Saxon king of England, 
at the Battle of Hastings. Harold was killed in the battle. William became king of England and is known as William the Conqueror. 
The battle is commemorated in a great piece of embroidery, known as the Bayeux Tapestry, which can still be seen in France today.
