The Boer War of 1899 to 1902 established the idea that the British Empire is a force for good
False
Incorrect	
The Boer War of 1899 to 1902 made the discussions about the future of the Empire more urgent. The British went to war in South 
Africa with settlers from the Netherlands called the Boers. The Boers fought fiercely and the war went on for over three years. 
Many died in the fighting and many more from disease. There was some public sympathy for the Boers and people began to question 
whether the Empire could continue.

