Why was the Habeas Corpus Act (1679) so important?
It guaranteed that no one could be held prisoner unlawfully
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Which TWO of these are English civil war battles?
Marston Moor
Naseby
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Incorrect	
During the civil war, the king’s army was defeated at the Battles of Marston Moor and Naseby. By 1646, it was 
clear that Parliament had won the war. Charles was held prisoner by the parliamentary army. He was still 
unwilling to reach any agreement with Parliament and in 1649 he was executed.

